Recovery Planning 8.1._full_text:
A financial institution shall prepare a recovery plan that consists of the following
components -

(a)
executive summary;

(b)
strategic analysis;

(c)
governance structure and oversight;

(d)
recovery indicators;

(e)
recovery options;

(f)
scenario analysis;

(g)
communication and disclosure plan; and

(h)
preparatory measures.
